for the quarter and year ended December 31, 2024.&#160; A copy of Linde plc&#8217;s press release is furnished herewith as Exhibit 99.1 and is hereby incorporated by reference in this Item 2.02.</p><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#160;</p><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>ITEM 9.01.&#160; Financial Statements and Exhibits.</strong></p><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#160;</p><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px;text-indent:36pt">(d) Exhibits. The following exhibit is furnished herewith pursuant to Item 2.02 hereof:</p><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#160;</p><table style="border-spacing:0;font-size:10pt;width:100%" cellpadding="0"><tbody><tr style="height:15px"><td style="BORDER-BOTTOM: 1px solid;width:8%;vertical-align:top;"><p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Exhibit&#160;No.</strong></p></td><td style="width:2%;"><p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:right;"><img src="linde_ex991img2.jpg"></p></td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Linde Reports Full-Year and Fourth-Quarter 2024 Results</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Full-Year Highlights</strong></p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;text-align:left;font:10pt times new roman;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="width:4%;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="width:4%;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Sales $33.0 billion, flat YoY, underlying sales up 2%</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Operating profit $8.6 billion; adjusted EPS $15.51, up 9% or 10% ex FX</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Returned $7.1 billion to shareholders through dividends and share repurchases</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Total project backlog of $10.4 billion</td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Fourth-Quarter Highlights</strong></p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;text-align:left;font:10pt times new roman;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="width:4%;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="width:4%;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Sales $8.3 billion, flat YoY, underlying sales up 2%</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Operating profit $2.3 billion, adjusted operating profit $2.5 billion, up 9%</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">Operating profit margin 27.4%; adjusted operating profit margin 29.9%, YoY up 250 basis points</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;">EPS $3.60, up 14%; adjusted EPS $3.97, up 11% or 13% ex FX</td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>2025 Guidance</strong></p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;text-align:left;font:10pt times new roman;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="width:4%;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="width:4%;vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">First-quarter 2025 adjusted EPS guidance $3.85 - $3.95, represents 7%-9% growth ex. FX</p></td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&#10146;</p></td> <td style="vertical-align:top;"> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">Full-year 2025 adjusted EPS guidance $16.15 - $16.55, represents 8%-11% growth ex. FX</p></td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Woking, UK, February 6, 2025 &#8211; Linde plc (Nasdaq: LIN) today reported fourth-quarter 2024 net income of $1,725 million and diluted earnings per share of $3.60, up 12% and 14% respectively.&nbsp; Excluding Linde AG purchase accounting impacts and other charges, adjusted net income was $1,899 million, up 8% versus prior year.&nbsp; Adjusted earnings per share was $3.97, 11% above prior year or 13% when excluding currency translation impact.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Linde&#8217;s sales for the fourth quarter were $8,282 million, flat versus prior year or 2% above when excluding negative currency impact.&nbsp; Compared to prior year, underlying sales increased 2% from price attainment and stable volumes.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Fourth-quarter operating profit was $2,270 million.&nbsp; Adjusted operating profit of $2,480 million was up 9% versus prior year led by higher price and continued productivity initiatives across all segments.&nbsp; Adjusted operating profit margin of 29.9% was 250 basis points above prior year.&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Fourth-quarter operating cash flow of $2,809 million increased 3% versus prior year. &nbsp;After capital expenditures of $1,250 million, free cash flow was $1,559 million.&nbsp; During the quarter, the company returned $1,990 million to shareholders through dividends and stock repurchases, net of issuances.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">For full-year 2024, sales were $33.0 billion, flat versus 2023.&nbsp; Compared to prior year, underlying sales increased 2% from 2% price attainment and stable volumes. &nbsp;Operating profit was $8.6 billion and adjusted operating profit was $9.7 billion, 7% above prior year. &nbsp;Adjusted operating profit margin was 29.5% of sales, 190 basis points higher than 2023.&nbsp; Diluted earnings per share was $13.62 and adjusted diluted earnings per share was $15.51, up 9% versus prior year or 10% when excluding currency translation impact.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">In 2024, Linde generated strong operating cash flow of $9.4 billion.&nbsp; The company invested $4.5 billion in capital expenditures and returned $7.1 billion to shareholders in the form of dividends and share buybacks, net of issuances. </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Commenting on the financial results and business outlook, Chief Executive Officer Sanjiv Lamba said, &#8220;In 2024, the Linde team once again delivered industry leading results, including a 25.9% ROC, 29.5% operating margin and an EPS growth of 10% excluding currency.&nbsp; The results were delivered despite the challenging environment, reflecting the resiliency of our model and the exceptional execution by our employees. &nbsp;We also made significant progress in our clean energy strategy, signing our largest ever product supply agreement with a high-quality customer, supporting the $10 billion project backlog which will contribute to earnings growth for years to come.&#8221;&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;font:10pt times new roman;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td class="hpbhr">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 1px solid; TEXT-INDENT: 0px;text-align:center;"> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">Page 1/10</p></td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td><p style='page-break-after: always'></p></td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;font-size:10pt;text-align:left;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="width:50%;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><img src="linde_ex991img3.jpg"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p></td> <td> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:right;"><img src="linde_ex991img2.jpg"></p></td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Lamba continued, &#8220;As anticipated, global macro conditions have continued to weaken, especially foreign currency translation.&nbsp; Regardless, I&#8217;m confident that with our disciplined capital allocation and focused management actions Linde will continue to deliver shareholder value.&#8221; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">For the full year 2025, the company expects adjusted diluted earnings per share to be in the range of $16.15 to $16.55, up 4% to 7% versus prior year or 8% to 11% when excluding estimated currency headwinds. &nbsp;Full-year capital expenditures are expected to range between $5 billion and $5.5 billion to support operating and growth requirements, including the contractual sale of gas backlog. &nbsp;For the first quarter 2025, adjusted earnings per share is expected to be in the range of $3.85 to $3.95, 3% to 5% above prior-year quarter or 7% to 9% when excluding 4% assumed unfavorable currency.&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Fourth-Quarter 2024 Results by Segment</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Americas sales of $3,609 million grew 1% versus prior-year quarter. &nbsp;Compared with fourth quarter 2023, underlying sales increased 3% driven by 2% higher pricing and 1% volumes, primarily in the manufacturing, electronics and food &amp; beverage end markets.&nbsp; Operating profit of $1,150 million was 31.9% of sales, 190 basis points above prior year.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">APAC (Asia Pacific) sales of $1,668 million were 2% above prior year.&nbsp; Compared to prior year, underlying sales grew 1% driven by project start-up volumes, primarily in the electronics end market.&nbsp; Operating profit of $500 million was 30.0% of sales, 240 basis points above prior year. &nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">EMEA (Europe, Middle East &amp; Africa) sales of $2,059 million were down 2% versus prior year.&nbsp; Compared with fourth-quarter 2023, underlying sales grew 1%, driven by 3% higher pricing partially offset by 2% lower volumes. &nbsp;Volumes were lower versus prior year, mainly in manufacturing and chemicals and energy end markets.&nbsp; Operating profit of $686 million was 33.3% of sales, 400 basis points above prior year.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Linde Engineering sales were $628 million, 5% below prior year, and operating profit was $106 million or 16.9% of sales.&nbsp; Order intake for the quarter was $880 million and third-party sale of equipment backlog was $3.3 billion. </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Earnings Call</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">A teleconference on Linde&#8217;s fourth-quarter 2024 results is being held today at 9:00 am EST.&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p on the website.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>About Linde</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">Linde is a leading global industrial gases and engineering company with 2024 sales of $33 billion.&nbsp; We live our mission of making our world more productive every day by providing high-quality solutions, technologies and services which are making our customers more successful and helping to sustain, decarbonize and protect our planet.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;font:10pt times new roman;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td class="hpbhr">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 1px solid; TEXT-INDENT: 0px;text-align:center;"> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; <td>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; MARGIN: 0px; text-align:left;">&nbsp;</p> <p style="margin:0px"> <table style="border-spacing:0;font-size:10pt;text-align:left;width:100%" cellpadding="0"> <tr style="height:15px"> <td style="width:50%;"> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><img src="linde_ex991img3.jpg"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p src="linde_ex991img2.jpg"></p></td></tr></table></p> <p style="margin:0px"></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">The company serves a variety of end markets such as chemicals &amp; energy, food &amp; beverage, electronics, healthcare, manufacturing, metals and mining. &nbsp;Linde's industrial gases and technologies are used in countless applications including production of clean hydrogen and carbon capture systems critical to the energy transition, life-saving medical oxygen and high-purity &amp; specialty gases for electronics. &nbsp;Linde also delivers state-of-the-art gas processing solutions to support customer expansion, efficiency improvements and emissions reductions.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">For more information about the company and its products and services, please visit www.linde.com</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p reconciliations and calculations for adjusted amounts.&nbsp; </p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new earnings per share (&#8220;EPS&#8221;) guidance for 2025. This is a non-GAAP financial measure that represents diluted earnings per share (a GAAP measure) but excludes the impact of certain items that we believe are not representative of our underlying business performance, such as cost reduction and other charges, the impact of potential divestitures or other potentially significant items. Given the uncertainty of timing and magnitude of such items, we cannot provide a reconciliation of the differences between the non-GAAP adjusted EPS guidance and the corresponding GAAP EPS measure without unreasonable effort.</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">&nbsp;</p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px"><strong>Forward-looking Statements</strong></p> <p style="font-size:10pt;font-family:times new roman;margin:0px">This document contains &#8220;forward-looking statements&#8221; within the meaning of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995.
